                                    By dispensing with all the atoms and only focusing on dislocation lines, the computational method of\par
                                    Discrete Dislocation Dynamics (DDD) gains greatly over Molecular Dynamics (MD) in simulation\par
                                    ef\u64257?ciency of metal plasticity. But whereas in MD dislocations follow natural dynamics of atomic\par
                                    motion, DDD must rely on a dislocation mobility function to prescribe how a dislocation line should\par
                  1234567890():,;\par
1234567890():,;\par
